Package: dbd-pg-pm-ssl
Version: 1.13
Revision: 3
BuildDepends: postgresql-ssl-dev (>= 7.2.3-1)
Depends: dbi-pm
Conflicts: dbd-pg-pm
Replaces: dbd-pg-pm
Suggests: postgresql-ssl
Source: http://www.cpan.org/modules/by-module/DBD/DBD-Pg-%v.tar.gz
UpdatePOD: true
Type: perl
DocFiles: README README.win32 MANIFEST Changes
GCC: 3.1
CompileScript: <<
  ranlib %p/lib/libpq.a
  POSTGRES_INCLUDE=%p/include/postgresql POSTGRES_LIB=%p/lib perl Makefile.PL PREFIX=%p INSTALLPRIVLIB=%p/lib/perl5 INSTALLARCHLIB=%p/lib/perl5/darwin INSTALLSITELIB=%p/lib/perl5 INSTALLSITEARCH=%p/lib/perl5/darwin INSTALLMAN1DIR=%p/share/man/man1 INSTALLMAN3DIR=%p/share/man/man3
  make
<<
InstallScript: <<
  make install INSTALLPRIVLIB=%i/lib/perl5 INSTALLARCHLIB=%i/lib/perl5/darwin INSTALLSITELIB=%i/lib/perl5 INSTALLSITEARCH=%i/lib/perl5/darwin INSTALLMAN1DIR=%i/share/man/man1 INSTALLMAN3DIR=%i/share/man/man3
  mkdir -p %i/share/doc/%n
  ln -s %p/lib/perl5/darwin/DBD/mysql.pod %i/share/doc/%n
<<
Description: Perl5 Database Interface to PostgreSQL (with SSL)
DescDetail: <<
DBD-Pg is a PostgreSQL interface for Perl5 using DBI.
For further information about DBI look at:
    http://dbi.symbolstone.org/
<<
DescPort: <<
Just like the DBD::mysql module, I couldn't use the default CompileScript
since 'make test' normally wouldn't pass: it needs a running postgresql
server with the necessary test databases set up correctly.

This links statically with postgresql, so it can be used as a client
without needing the postgresql shared libs installed.
<<
